    "created_at": "2016-03-09T00:16:07Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-03-09T00:18:20Z",
    "body": "@bengotow Have a look at my screenshot in the first comment. I don't think your approach would work for that use case (Preference windows like this are a reasonably common screen on OS X).\n\nI think it's best to decouple the offset of the sheets from the offset of the buttons if it's possible? If you want to couple them then it's trivial to do it in Javascript. Perhaps I'm missing some of the reasoning behind the coupling though.\n"
