    "created_at": "2016-03-09T11:44:57Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-03-09T11:49:35Z",
    "body": "`titleBarHeight` sounds nice and declarative but it also seems a bit implicit if the only effect of the property is to offset sheet dialogs. If this is the case I would probably be in favour of something more explicit like `sheetVerticalOffset` but not strongly so. I understand `sheetVerticalOffset` sounds ugly and non-declarative but it more directly describe the effect of setting the property.\n\nI take your point about the BrowserWindow config becoming a bit of a mess. Another possibility is to move the option to `dialog.showX()` instead? I'm not sure how I feel about that but it does add more flexibility [1] when you define the sheet offset directly at the call site. I don't really have an opinion on this but it's worth considering at least.\n\n[1] e.g. if the titlebar height changes on the UI or you want to do something crazy like a sheet within a sheet.\n"
  },
